  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Early Childhood Development Program for Children Affected by HIV/AIDS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CHWs provide a monthly training sessions to each caregiver group in nutrition education and specific age-appropriate feeding ,Cooking demonstrations to caregiver groups,Training and seeds to caregivers to start kitchen gardens and boost maize production,Training of Savings Faciitators,Training of ZAC staff on SLA, Training of Volunteer Savings Group Facilitators,Formation of Savings Groups,Training volunteers to be psychosocial counselors ,Facilitate playgroups for 3-5 yr. olds using preschool curriculum,Preschool curriculum training for ECD volunteers,EP Training for new staff and new volunteers ,Stakeholders&apos; Orientations to EP and ECD project,Participation in Zambia National ECD Committee meetings, Hilton partner meeting, ECD &amp;amp; HIV/AIDS Sector workshops,Facilitate twice a month meetings of Caregiver Support &amp;amp; Learning Groups &amp;amp; toddler playgroups ,Monthly home visits to 7,070 families.,CHWs provide one health education session quarterly for each caregiver group ,Equip Centers with age appropriate hand washing stations, rehabilitation of existing latrines at centers as needed ,WASH education sessions facilitated with Caregiver groups,Monthly growth monitoring (BMI) of 12,446 children, including nutrition focus, and make referrals to health facilities as needed.</narrative>
  </description>
